---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Entry Point";
const description =
  "Send one link: the projectâ€™s entry point page that maps to everything else.";
const permalink = new URL("/entry-point", Astro.site!).href;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  permalink={permalink}
  current="entry-point"
>
  <h1>Entry Point</h1>

  <style>
    .tldr {
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #ddd);
      background: var(--color-bg-soft, #f9f9f9);
      padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .subtle {
      color: var(--color-text-dim, #666);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
      font-weight: 400;
    }
    .section {
      margin: 1.25rem 0;
    }
    .examples code {
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="tldr" role="note" aria-label="TL;DR">
    ðŸ‘‰ TL;DR: Send exactly <strong>one link</strong> â€” the page that maps to everything
    else.
    <div class="subtle">
      Not a bundle of URLs. One page that already collects them.
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Hello! If I shared this link with you, Iâ€™m asking:
    <strong>Where is the projectâ€™s entry point?</strong>
  </p>

  <p>
    The entry point is a single page that acts as the project map. It links to
    the essentials and is the first thing a newcomer should read.
  </p>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What belongs on an entry point page</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Repository or code (<strong>README</strong> or equivalent)</li>
      <li>Task board (Jira, Trello, Linear)</li>
      <li>Documentation (Confluence, Notion, wiki)</li>
      <li>Meeting notes and decisions</li>
      <li>Key contacts and responsibilities</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="subtle">Think of it as the table of contents for the project.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Why one link matters</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Onboarding is faster. Open one page, not five tabs.</li>
      <li>Fewer pings. No scavenger hunts for scattered links.</li>
      <li>Shared reality. Update once, align everyone.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section examples">
    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Repo-driven project: the <code>README</code> is the entry point.</li>
      <li>
        Non-technical project: a single Confluence, Notion, or Google Doc.
      </li>
      <li>
        Cross-team effort: an index page that links Jira, docs, dashboards, and
        notes.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What I need from you</h2>
    <p>
      If the project already has an entry point, please send me that one link.
      If it does not exist yet, create a short page with the links above and
      share it. It does not need to be fancy. It does need to exist.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
